3. The Execution Sandbox (How the AI "Runs" Code)
If you want the AI to write a script and then execute it right there in the environment, you cannot run that code directly on your main server (for security reasons).

Client-Side Approach (WebContainers): Use the WebContainers API (by StackBlitz). This allows you to run a full Node.js environment directly inside the user's browser. The AI writes the code, pushes it to the WebContainer, and runs it instantly without server overhead.

Server-Side Approach (Docker): Set up an ephemeral Docker container architecture. When you ask Kaixu to execute Python or Node code, your backend spins up an isolated Docker container, runs the AI's code, returns the terminal output to your chat window, and then destroys the container.

